24/11/2006
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Croatian Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic arrived in Kabul on Thursday (November 23rd) to inspect his country's contingent within the International Security Assistance Force (ISAF). 
He reiterated Croatia's commitment to continue participation in the mission, noting efforts against smugglers and those planting explosive devices. 
Roncevic also met with Afghanistan's ministers of foreign and internal affairs.
In other news, the strike is Croatia's educational sector expanded on Thursday when high school teachers joined their colleagues from primary schools in demanding higher salaries. 
Reportedly some 90% of all teachers are now participating. 
On Friday, university professors staged protests. 
(Vjesnik - 24/11/06; HINA, HRT - 23/11/06)
